Mergers & Acquisitions Director
Job Seekers
|
|
what:
where:
Leap29
-
Dubai
A suitable candidate will be responsible for leading the organisation's M&A; strategy in every stage - sourcing, screening, due diligence, structuring transactions and closing. They will also be involved in periodic reviews, updates to the M&A; strategy, budgeting for the M&A; activities, develop and maintain internal processes and develop strong relationships with all parties involved.
In order to be successful a candidate must have:
- Bachelor Degree in a relevant discipline - Masters Degree in a relevant discipline - 15-20 years of experience in a related role, with leadership experience - Experience in all stages of M&A; transactions - At least 7 years of experience in M&A; within an Oil & Gas company - Deal experience in the downstream Oil & Gas sector - International experience - leading transactions - preferably Middle East, North Africa, Africa and Central Asia - Strong negotiation skills - Excellent English speaking abilities is a must with Arabic speaking abilities being a preference
This is an opportunity to join a leading organisation in a rapidly growing market and the chance to work with an enthusiastic team.
If you possess the necessary skills required, please apply using the links provided. Alternatively, send your CV to ngorse@leap29.com
